(503, 'Notes from Notion AI: Chanakya discussed his Up&Run electrolyte drink business with an investor/advisor Rahul, sharing details about the product, business metrics, and fundraising strategy.
Product & Background: - Sugar-free hydration product similar to US brand Element (99% identical formulation) - Created after 6 months of R&D using family''s medical network to find manufacturers - Working with same manufacturers as TWT, establishing a second manufacturing line - Patent filed for the formulation in India - Founder is a distance runner who was an Element consumer
Business Traction: - Live on Blinkit in Maharashtra since February 2025 - Also on Amazon, Flipkart, and soon on Clinically (PO being finalized) - Selling ~100 units/month on Blinkit, ~80 units/month on website - AOV: ₹400 on Blinkit, ₹600 on website - Current monthly revenue: ~₹1.5L (₹50K from website, ₹50K from Blinkit, ₹10-20K from other channels) - All growth has been organic so far (no paid marketing)
Fundraising Strategy: - Rahul advised reaching ₹10-15L monthly sales before approaching institutional investors - Recommended a friends & family round of ₹1-1.5 crore - Suggested valuation of ~₹10 crore (15% max dilution) - Recommended avoiding predatory offers (had received ₹1 crore for 50% equity offer) - Founder should retain ~25% after multiple funding rounds
Action Items: - [ ] Chanakya to send list of potential angel investors who are already customers - [ ] Chanakya to share a short business description for i...')
